      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "My apologies for the confusion. An escrow account in the context of a house purchase is a neutral third-party account that holds the buyer's deposit and other funds until the closing of the sale. The escrow company acts as a neutral party to ensure that all conditions of the sale are met before the funds are released to the seller and the property title is transferred to the buyer. The buyer's funds are typically held in escrow until the closing date, at which point the funds are released to the seller, and the buyer's funds are used to pay the seller's outstanding debts, such as the mortgage, and to cover closing costs. The escrow account ensures that both parties fulfill their obligations before the transaction is completed.",
